NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the line of play, Irene got it basically right. She wants to set up clubs but, at trick 4, she should play the @C9 right away to preserve all her heart entries. That was a minor issue and turned out not to cost. But an expert player, if they had AKx of clubs, might have ducked, and then Irene could conceivably have been an entry short. Although on this hand, because of the club holding it turned out not to matter.|
